article.headline: Alabama A&M 87, Paul Quinn 59
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Cornelius Hester scored a game-high 25 points and was 7-of-11 from the three-point mark to lead Alabama A&M to a 87-59 win over Paul Quinn Saturday night. The Bulldogs built a 53-18 lead by the half and never trailed in the game. Three Alabama A&M had three players come off the bench to score in double figures. Johnnie Brown scored 16 points, Trant Simpson had 13 and Jonathan Belt added 10. Mickell Gladness had nine of the team's 14 blocked shots against the Tigers. Simpson led the Bulldogs in rebounds with eight and assists with nine. Paul Quinn shot just 28.6 percent from the floor and hit only 1-13 from the three-point line. Damien Chisholm led the Tigers with 13 points.
